% B6c -- raiseerror with a non-empty ostack.
% Five operands are on the operand stack when the error fires.
% raiseerror's ostack snapshot (recordstacks=true) copies all of
% them; cleartomark restores the stack between iterations so the
% loop's net stack effect is zero.
tic 1000000 { mark 1 2 3 4 5 { /test /Bench raiseerror } stopped { handleerror } if counttomark 1 add_ii npop } repeat toc ==
% NB: counttomark/npop kept because B6c intentionally pushes 5 ints (deep
% ostack at error time) and needs to drop them between iterations.
quit
